    start=start_time,

)

Portfolio Optimization

In[287]:
return_factor = 1.2

combined_stocks = np.array(
    [
        df_train[df_train["symbol"]==symbols[0]]["daily_return"].values, 
        df_train[df_train["symbol"]==symbols[1]]["daily_return"].values, 
        df_train[df_train["symbol"]==symbols[2]]["daily_return"].values, 
        df_train[df_train["symbol"]==symbols[3]]["daily_return"].values,
    ]
)[:,1:]

r1 = np.nanmean(df_train[df_train["symbol"]==symbols[0]]["daily_return"].values)
r2 = np.nanmean(df_train[df_train["symbol"]==symbols[1]]["daily_return"].values)
r3 = np.nanmean(df_train[df_train["symbol"]==symbols[2]]["daily_return"].values)
r4 = np.nanmean(df_train[df_train["symbol"]==symbols[3]]["daily_return"].values)
r_avg = np.array([r1, r2, r3, r4])

s1 = np.nanstd(df_train[df_train["symbol"]==symbols[0]]["daily_return"].values)
s2 = np.nanstd(df_train[df_train["symbol"]==symbols[1]]["daily_return"].values)
s3 = np.nanstd(df_train[df_train["symbol"]==symbols[2]]["daily_return"].values)
s4 = np.nanstd(df_train[df_train["symbol"]==symbols[3]]["daily_return"].values)
var = np.array([s1**2,s2**2,s3**2,s4**2])

cov_matrix = np.cov(combined_stocks)

target_return = np.mean(r_avg)*return_factor

# --- Step 4: Define optimization variables ---
w = cp.Variable(4)

# --- Step 5: Define objective (minimize variance) ---
portfolio_variance = cp.quad_form(w, cov_matrix)

# --- Step 6: Constraints ---
constraints = [
    cp.sum(w) == 1,         # weights sum to 1
    r_avg @ w == target_return  # expected return constraint
]

# --- Step 7: Solve the optimization problem ---
prob = cp.Problem(cp.Minimize(portfolio_variance), constraints)
prob.solve()

# --- Step 8: Extract weights ---
weights = w.value
print("Optimal Weights:")
for idx, i in enumerate(symbols):
    print(f"{i}: {weights[idx]}")
print()
print("Minimum Portfolio Variance:", prob.value)

Beta Calculation

In[296]:
betas = {}
for name, data in stock_data.groupby("symbol"):
    cov_mat = np.cov(np.array([benchmark_data["daily_return"].dropna(), data["daily_return"].dropna()]))
    cov_ = cov_mat[0,1]
    var_ = np.nanstd(np.array([benchmark_data["daily_return"]]))**2
    betas[name] = cov_/var_
    print(f"{name} Beta: {cov_/var_:0.03f}")

portfolio_beta = 0
for beta, weight in zip(betas.values(), weights):
    portfolio_beta += beta*weight

print()
print(f"Portfolio Beta: {portfolio_beta:0.03f}")

Sharpe Ratio and Jensen Index Calculation

In[297]:
def sharpe_ratio(rp, rf, sigma):
    return (rp-rf)/sigma

def jensen_index(ri, rm, rf, beta):
    return ri - (rf + beta*(rm-rf))

market_return = np.nanmean(benchmark_data_test["close"].pct_change())
sharpe_ = sharpe_ratio(overall_return, rf=risk_free, sigma=overall_risk)
alpha = jensen_index(ri=overall_return, rm=market_return, rf=risk_free, beta=portfolio_beta)

print(f"Sharpe Ratio for this Portfolio: {sharpe_:0.03f}")
print(f"Jensen Index (alpha) for this Portfolio: {alpha:0.03f}")

Sharpe Ratio for this Portfolio: 9.332

In[298]:
VaR_portfolio_returns = testing_data.pct_change().dropna().values

mu, sigma = norm.fit(VaR_portfolio_returns)

# Calculate the mean and standard error of the mean (SEM) of the data
mean = np.mean(VaR_portfolio_returns)
# Calculate the standard deviation (using ddof=1 for sample standard deviation)
std_dev = np.std(VaR_portfolio_returns, ddof=1) 

# Get the size of the data
n = np.size(VaR_portfolio_returns)

# Calculate the SEM
sem_ = std_dev / np.sqrt(n)

# Calculate the 95% confidence interval
confidence_interval = norm.interval(0.99, loc=mu, scale=sigma)

plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))
plt.hist(VaR_portfolio_returns, bins=10, density=True, edgecolor='black', alpha=0.4, color='b', label='Data Histogram')
plt.xlim(-0.02, 0.025)

xmin, xmax = plt.xlim()
x = np.linspace(xmin, xmax, 100)
p = norm.pdf(x, mu, sigma)
plt.plot(x, p, 'k', linewidth=2, label='Fitted Normal PDF')

plt.title(f"Value at Risk: 99% Lower CI = {abs(confidence_interval[0])*100:.3f}%")
plt.xlabel("Value") 
plt.ylabel("Density")
plt.legend()
plt.show()

print(f"Based on Value at Risk with a 99% CI we could expect at most to lose {abs(confidence_interval[0])*100:.2f}% of the portfolio in a day (${abs(confidence_interval[0])*portfolio_value:,.2f}).")
